{"questionId":"17420","questionHtml":"<p>Find the critical region for Josie’s test, giving your answer correct to two decimal&nbsp;places.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>under&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"{H_0}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>H</mi> <mn>0</mn> </msub> </mrow> </math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\bar X \\sim {\\text{N}}\\left( {60{\\text{, }}\\frac{4}{{100}}} \\right)\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mover> <mi>X</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">¯</mo> </mover> </mrow> <mo>∼</mo> <mrow> <mtext>N</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mn>60</mn> <mrow> <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext> </mrow> <mfrac> <mn>4</mn> <mrow> <mn>100</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>required to find <span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"k\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>k</mi> </math></span> such that&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"P\\left( {\\bar X > k} \\right) = 0.05\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>P</mi> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mrow> <mover> <mi>X</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">¯</mo> </mover> </mrow> <mo>&gt;</mo> <mi>k</mi> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0.05</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>use of any valid method, <em>eg</em> GDC Inv(Normal) or&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"k = 60 + z\\frac{\\sigma }{{\\sqrt n }}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>k</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>60</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mi>z</mi> <mfrac> <mi>σ</mi> <mrow> <msqrt> <mi>n</mi> </msqrt> </mrow> </mfrac> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence critical region is&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\bar x = 60.33\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mover> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">¯</mo> </mover> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>60.33</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17420","referenceCode":"19N.3.AHL.TZ0.Hsp_3c.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the critical region for Josie’s test, giving your answer correct to two decimal places.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"c.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.18—T and Z test, type I and II errors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}